			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Lithium hydroxide (LiOH) is an inorganic compound used in making lithium salts of stearic and other fatty acids, which are used as thickeners in lubricating greases. It is also used as an additive. It can exist in a hydrated form as well as in an anhydrous form and both forms are white hygroscopic solids. LiOH is a weak alkali metal but is a strong base at the same time.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氢氧化锂（LiOH）是一种无机化合物，用于制造硬脂酸和其他脂肪酸的锂盐，在润滑脂中用作增稠剂。它还可用作添加剂。它既可以水合形式存在，也可以无水形式存在，两种形式都是白色吸湿性固体。LiOH 是一种弱碱金属，但同时也是一种强碱。</common:generalComment>
